<item>
            <title>[FELIX-137] ServiceDependency fails to invoke callback methods when implemented in superclass (patch included)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-137</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ServiceDependency fails to invoke callback methods when implemented in superclass. The problem is in the invokeCallbackMethod method cause it will never loop. I include 2 patches. The first just fixes the loop, but I was wondering why getDeclaredMethod is used. Using getMethod instead seems to work just fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;grz,&lt;br/&gt;
Bram&lt;/p&gt;</description>
