                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12432358" author="marrs" created="Sun, 3 Sep 2006 17:37:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patches, Bram! I&apos;m going to combine them to make sure that callbacks are found regardless of their exact location. getDeclaredMethod() was used because it can also find non-public methods (which getMethod() can&apos;t) but on the other hand, getDeclaredMethod() cannot find methods in superclasses. I would really want both, so I&apos;ll come up with a patch that does just that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12432545" author="marrs" created="Mon, 4 Sep 2006 20:26:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just committed a patch that implements a new algorithm to invoke methods in any (super)class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12455957" author="bramk" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2006 10:23:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems now it is all little too enthusiastic &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/tongue.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; In my case I now get multiple callbacks on from servicedependencies in the same scenario. The problem is in the recursive invokeMethod that takes a depth first approach and doesn&apos;t stop when it&apos;s done. I&apos;ll attach a new patch to this problem. It&apos;s non-recursive and breadth first.. I like it &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12455958" author="bramk" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2006 10:25:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fix for multiple callbacks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;removes recursion&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;changes approach to breadth first&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12456225" author="marrs" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2006 21:44:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still not correctly implemented, incorporate Bram&apos;s fixes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12456256" author="marrs" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2006 23:24:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch supplied by Bram.&lt;br/&gt;
Added one extra option to make sure that the method stops looking for a method if the invoked method itself throws an exception (which means we did find and invoke the method, it just did not complete normally).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12471926" author="rickhall" created="Sat, 10 Feb 2007 02:52:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk closing all of these resolved issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
